Kuzbass Fuel Heads for 10-Month Low on 66 Percent Drop in Profit

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-08-24T10:05:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/kuzbass-fuel-heads-for-10-month-low-on-66-percent-drop-in-profit.html
Kuzbass Fuel Co. headed for its
lowest close since October after the Russian producer of coal
for power stations said second-quarter profit declined 66
percent from the previous three-month period.  The shares slid 3.1 percent to 170.64 rubles by 1:49 p.m.
in Moscow, poised for their weakest level since Oct. 25.  Net income dropped to 200 million rubles ($6.9 million)
from 593 million rubles in first quarter, Kuzbass said today in
an e-mailed statement. Revenue fell 6 percent to 4.94 billion
rubles.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  